# 1. What were your favourite activities when you were a child?

When I was a child, I was really into outdoor activities, especially playing basketball and riding bicycles with my friends. After school, we would spend hours running around the neighborhood, which was both exciting and relaxing. Besides that, I also loved playing video games because they gave me a sense of achievement and curiosity about technology. Looking back, I think those activities made my childhood much more energetic and memorable.

### 中文翻译：

我小时候特别喜欢户外活动，尤其是和朋友一起打篮球、骑自行车。放学后，我们经常在小区里玩上好几个小时，那种感觉既开心又放松。除此之外，我也很喜欢玩电子游戏，因为它们会给我一种成就感，同时也激发了我对科技的兴趣。现在回想起来，我觉得这些活动让我的童年更加充满活力，也更值得怀念。

---

# 2. Did you prefer to do activities alone or with a group of people when you were a child?

I definitely preferred doing activities with a group of people when I was younger. I was quite active as a child, so I enjoyed team activities like basketball, hide-and-seek or simply hanging out with classmates. Being with friends made everything more fun and competitive. However, there were also times when I liked being alone, especially when playing computer games or reading comics. So I’d say I mostly enjoyed group activities, but I still needed some personal space occasionally.

### 中文翻译：

我小时候肯定更喜欢和一群人一起活动。我那时候性格挺活跃的，所以很喜欢像篮球、捉迷藏，或者和同学一起玩的活动。和朋友待在一起会让所有事情都变得更有趣，也更有竞争感。不过有时候我也喜欢独处，比如玩电脑游戏或者看漫画。所以我会说，我大多数时候喜欢集体活动，但偶尔也需要一点自己的空间。

---

# 3. Do you think children today play the same games as you did when you were a child?

Not really. I think children nowadays spend much more time on smartphones, tablets and online games compared with my generation. When I was young, we still played many traditional outdoor games, so we had more face-to-face interaction and physical activity. Of course, some classic games are still popular, but technology has clearly changed the way children entertain themselves. In my opinion, modern games are more convenient and advanced, but sometimes children today may miss out on real-world social experiences.

### 中文翻译：

不完全是。我觉得现在的孩子比我们那一代花更多时间在手机、平板以及网络游戏上。我小时候还会经常玩很多传统的户外游戏，所以人与人之间的面对面交流和身体活动会更多。当然，有些经典游戏现在依然流行，不过科技确实改变了孩子们娱乐的方式。在我看来，现代游戏虽然更方便、更先进，但有时候现在的孩子可能会错过一些真实世界中的社交体验。
